# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully implemented Vercel Speed Insights for the devsense-frontend project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` v1.3.1 to project dependencies
- Updated package.json and package-lock.json

### 2. Modified Files
- **src/App.jsx**: Added SpeedInsights component
  - Imported `SpeedInsights` from `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the Vercel Speed Insights documentation for React applications:
- Used the React-specific package (`@vercel/speed-insights/react`)
- Added the component at the app root level in App.jsx
- Placed it alongside the existing Vercel Analytics component for consistency

## Build Verification

- ✅ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
- ✅ No new linting errors introduced (existing errors were pre-existing)
- ✅ Package installation successful with no vulnerabilities

## Next Steps

After deploying to Vercel:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard for this project
2. The `/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js` route will be automatically added
3. Performance metrics will begin tracking after deployment and user visits
4. Data can be viewed in the Vercel dashboard under the "Speed Insights" tab

## Notes

- The project already had `@vercel/analytics` installed, so Speed Insights was added in a similar pattern
- Speed Insights will only function when deployed to Vercel's platform
- No additional configuration is required as the component uses sensible defaults
